Acer has launched new gaming hardware, as well as updated versions of some of its most popular gaming PCs and laptops. The new gaming hardware includes new Nitro 50 gaming desktops, two new monitors, and a new gaming mouse. Acer also announced that it will be refreshing its Predator Orion 9000 and Orion 3000 desktop rigs, as well as four of its most popular gaming laptops. These laptops now offer 10th-generation Intel Core H-series processors and improved RTX graphics – allowing users to access desktop-like performance in a mobile form factor. Acer said it has also equipped these notebooks with improved thermal designs, new cooling techniques, and more heat pipes. The new hardware will be available on the following dates at the following prices: These updated gaming laptops will be available on the following dates at the following prices: The Acer Nitro 50 series is designed to deliver powerful performance for casual gamers and beginners. These computers will sport up to a 10th-generation Intel Core i7 processor and up to a Geforce RTX 2060 Super GPU. It will offer up to 64GB DDR4 2,666 MHz memory, 1TB NVMe SSD storage, and two 3TB HDDs. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-357297" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Nitro-50-640x430.jpg" alt="Nitro 50" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Nitro-50-640x430.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Nitro-50-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Nitro-50-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Nitro-50-768x516.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Nitro-50-1536x1032.jpg 1536w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Nitro-50-1200x806.jpg 1200w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Nitro-50.jpg 1860w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-widt